Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a large #pan{} over medium-high
heat. Add @Tex-Mex Ground Plant-Based Protein{8%ounce}. Using a #spatula{},
press into an even layer; cook, undisturbed, until browned on
bottom, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> TIP: If protein starts popping, cover with a lid.

Break up protein into pieces and cook until browned all
over and warmed through, ~{3-4%minutes} more.

Turn off heat; using a #slotted spoon{}, transfer to a #medium bowl{}. Stir in
@cream cheese{6%tablespoon} until melted and thoroughly
combined. Wash out pan.

Lay @flour tortillas{2} on a clean work surface. Top one half of each
tortilla with filling and sprinkle with @Monterey Jack Cheese{1/4%cup}. Fold
tortillas in half to create quesadillas.

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} and a drizzle of oil in pan used for filling over medium-high heat.

> 2 TBSP butter for 4 servings.

Add quesadillas; cook until tortillas are golden brown
and cheese melts, ~{2-4%minutes} per side.

> Depending on the size of your pan, you may need to work in batches.

Cut quesadillas into thirds and divide between plates. Serve with
@pico de gallo{4%ounce} and @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon} on the side.

> Plant-based protein is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165º.